        </td></tr>
        <tr><td>
<a class="key" href="../de.htm"><div  data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Shortcut to Germany (BRD)" class="key">Germany</div></a><a class="key" href="../fr.htm"><div  data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Shortcut to France" class="key">France</div></a><a class="key" href="../coldwar.htm"><div  data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Shortcut to Cold War" class="key">Cold War</div></a><a class="key" href="../../manuf/telefunken"><div  data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Shortcut to Telefunken" class="key">Telefunken</div></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="key" href="../esk52/index.htm"><div  data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Forward to ESK-52" class="key right">ESK-52 &rarr;</div></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;        <div style="height: 20px;"></div>
        <table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
          <tr><td height=4><img src="../../img/blank.gif" width=1 height=4></td></tr>
          <tr>
          <td align="left" valign="center">
          <font size="+1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#F52E00>
          <b>B2M</b>
          </font>
          </td>
          </tr>
          <tr><td colspan=2 height=1><img src=../../img/blank.gif width=1 height=1></td></tr>
          <tr><td height=4><img src="../../img/blank.gif" width=1 height=4></td></tr>
        </table>
        <table width=100% border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
          <tr>
          <td valign=top align=left>
          <font size="-1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#555555>
<b>German spy radio set (B2 clone)</b>
<font color=#F52E00>- this page is a stub</font>
<br />
<br />
<b>B2M</b>, codenamed <b>MITCHELL</b>, is a
<a href="../index.htm"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: spy radio set">spy radio set</span></a>, developed in 1946 by
<a href="../../manuf/telefunken/index.htm"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: Telefunken">Telefunken</span></a> in Hannover (Germany),
for use by <a href="../../intel/index.htm"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: intelligence services">intelligence services</span></a>
and <a href="../sbo/index.htm"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: Stay-Behind Organisations (SBO)">Stay-Behind Organisations (SBO)</span></a>
in post-war Europe. It is a direct clone of the British
<a href="../b2"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: Type 3 Mark II (B2)">Type 3 Mark II (B2)</span></a>, albeit built with German parts.
The device was succeeded in 1952 by the similar <a href="../esk52"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: ESK-52">ESK-52</span></a>,
which was nicknamed <i>Amateur Radio Set</i>.
          </font>
          </td></tr>
        </table>
<br />        <table width=100% border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
          <tr>
          <td valign=top align=left>
          <font size="-1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#555555>
The device is housed in a
<a href="img/304028/016/full.jpg"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: heavy wooden enclo&shy;sure">heavy wooden enclo&shy;sure</span></a> that also acts
as a transport case. It has a leather grip at the top and a
<a href="img/304028/014/full.jpg"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: removable lid at the front">removable lid at the front</span></a>,
that is held in place by two hinges
at the bottom and two spring-loaded clips at the top.
<br />
<br />
The B2M is a clone of the British <a href="../b2"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: Type 3 Mark II">Type 3 Mark II</span></a>, commonly known
as the <a href="../b2"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: B2">B2</span></a>, but unlike the <a href="../b2"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: B2">B2</span></a> &ndash; which consists of three
separate units &ndash; the B2M is an <a href="img/304028/011/full.jpg"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: all-in-one device">all-in-one device</span></a>.
At the front panel,
the individual units &ndash; transmitter, receiver and <span class="short tooltip-red" data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Power Supply Unit">PSU</span> &ndash; are separated by
white lines. <a href="img/304028/001/full.jpg"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: On the inside">On the inside</span></a> how&shy;ever, the
three individual units are still visible.
          </font></td>
          <td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
          <td align=center valign=top width=100>
          <table 
           border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" ><tr><td align="center" valign=top>
<a href="img/304028/013/full.jpg">            <div style="position: relative;" data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="B2M in wooden suitcase">
<a href="img/304028/013/full.jpg">            <div style="position: relative;" data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="B2M in wooden suitcase">
            <img src="img/304028/013/small.jpg"
             style="
             max-width: 618px;
            "
             align="left"
             vspace="4"
             alt="B2M in wooden suitcase"
             border=0
             width=298 height=200
             />
            </div>
            </a>
            </td></tr><tr><td align=center>
          </td></tr></table>
          </td></tr>
        </table>
<br />        <table width=100% border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
          <tr>
          <td valign=top align=left>
          <font size="-1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#555555>
Like the <a href="../b2"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: B2">B2</span></a>, the B2M comes with a set of
<a href="img/304028/005/full.jpg"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: plug-in coils">plug-in coils</span></a>
for the various frequency ranges. The desired coil must be installed
in the socket marked 'X' at the <a href="img/304028/002/full.jpg"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: front panel">front panel</span></a>.
Unused coils are <a href="img/304028/003/full.jpg"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: stowed on a wooden frame">stowed on a wooden frame</span></a>
that is kept in the
<a href="img/304028/012/full.jpg"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: accessory compartment at the right">accessory compartment at the right</span></a>.
Other items that are provided in the
<a href="img/304028/012/full.jpg"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: accessory compartment">accessory compartment</span></a> are a
<a href="img/304028/010/full.jpg"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: screwdriver">screwdriver</span></a>, <a href="img/304028/006/full.jpg"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: morse keys">morse keys</span></a>,
<a href="img/304028/007/full.jpg"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: headphones">headphones</span></a>,
<a href="img/304028/009/full.jpg"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: spare valves and a spare vibrator ...">spare valves and a spare vibrator pack</span></a>
and <a href="img/304028/008/full.jpg"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: power cables">power cables</span></a>.
The B2M was succeeded in 1952 by the <a href="../esk52"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: ESK-52">ESK-52</span></a>.
          </font>
          </td></tr>
        </table>
<br />        <div style="background-color: #EEEEEE; font-size: 8pt; padding: 12px; color: #777777; overflow: auto;">
<font color=#F52E00>PLEASE HELP &mdash;</font>
This page currently acts as a placeholder for information about the German
B2M spy radio set. Crypto Museum does not have a B2M in its collection.
You can help us to improve this page by providing additional information.
<font color="#E7E">&#10148;</font>&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info@cryptomuseum.com">Contact us</a>
        </div>
