          <tr><td height=4><img src="../../img/blank.gif" width=1 height=4></td></tr>
          <tr>
          <td align="left" valign="center">
          <font size="+1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#F52E00>
          <b>Audio samples</b>
          </font>
          </td>
          </tr>
          <tr><td colspan=2 height=1><img src=../../img/blank.gif width=1 height=1></td></tr>
          <tr><td height=4><img src="../../img/blank.gif" width=1 height=4></td></tr>
        </table>
        <table width=100% border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
          <tr>
          <td valign=top align=left>
          <font size="-1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#555555>
In February 2018, German radio amateur Karsten Hansky (DR3HRT),
recorded the audio samples below. The first sample was taken from
the receiver of the B2M, whilst connected to a long-wire antenna.
The second sample is from the B2M's own transmitter, recorded
approx. 400 km away via the Web-SDR receiver at Twente University
in the Netherlands.
          </font>
          </td></tr>
        </table>
